Miss Stiviano, who has described herself as being his 'confidante and friend', has denied releasing the tapes.

NBA Commissioner Adam Silver has since banned Mr Sterling for life and fined him $2.5 million.

During a television interview with CNN’s Anderson Cooper, Mr Sterling started by apologising for his racist comments.

But as the interview progressed he blamed the media for blowing his words out of proportion before going on an angry attack against Magic Johnson, one of the targets of his racist remarks.

